+---
+name: crush-android-play-release
+description: Crush.lu Android Play Console release status: v1.0.1 is live to internal testers; Luxembourg open test remains in review
+type: project
+source: codex
+updated: 2026-07-16
+tags: [crush, android, release, roadmap]
+---
+
+Play Console was checked directly on 2026-07-16. Crush.lu package
+`lu.crush.app`, version `1.0.1` (version code `2`), is **available to
+internal testers** at full rollout. The active bundle was uploaded on
+2026-07-06 at 16:14; version `1.0.0` / code `1` is inactive.
+
+The broader **open testing** release is configured for Luxembourg and has
+been **In review** since submission on 2026-07-06 at 18:30. That submission
+also includes production country coverage, the Alpha closed-test setup,
+store listing, app-content declarations, and store settings. Production is
+still inactive; its release remains a draft. Installed audience and install
+base were both 0% when checked. Until review completes, internal testers see
+the temporary name `lu.crush.app (unreviewed)`.
+
+The Alpha closed-test track has Luxembourg selected and an email-list tester
+group named `CrushCoachs`, but the track is inactive. The Play Console account
+reports all apps successfully registered for Android developer verification.
+
+**Why:** Android is one of Tom's active Crush.lu launch tracks, and agents
+must distinguish the successful internal test deployment from the still-
+pending open-test/store review and the inactive production release.
+**How to apply:** treat internal testing as ready for device testing; next
+check the review result, enroll real testers and collect install/auth/upload
+results before preparing production. Keep Android release docs aligned with
+the actual `1.0.1` / code `2`. Related: [[crush-current-focus]],
+[[crush-android-signing]].
